<br>
&lt;&lt;Quest Start:<br>
In the First Plane of Air, talk to Paladin Quest NPC and hand in a book, to get the Dwarf Dirkog to Spawn.<br>
<br>
<br>
Ok, to be clearer. I don't understand the above line. To me, it says the start of the quest is in Plane of Air, where, in POA, you have to hand in a book to get the Dwarf Dirkog to Spawn. I know about the Book of Scales for the lich, but what's this about a book in the PoA?&gt;&gt;<br>
<br>
To answer this there is an efreeti up there in the quest hall with the last name goldblade, tell him you wish to be tested by dirkog steelhand, he will hand you a book, return the same book to him and he despawns, and dirkog steelhand spawns in his place, that is the NPC which you give the 500 platinum to in order to spawn Inte Akera.<br>
<br>
</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#666666><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uragnorath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ragnorath</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>4/6/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>10:40:08 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Efreeti's name</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Well after spending 45 minutes tonight trying to figure out which efreeti to talk to, I figure that the name might be good information for all the other paladins out there trying to get FA.<br>
<br>
You want to have someone hail Dason Goldblade in the POA quest hall.  Best thing is to ask a high level wizard buddy to come up to POA just as you get ready to kill Gorgolask on the palace island (this will cost you 240pp for the POA stone, but it is worth the price).  Once Gorgolask is killed and you have your key to the windmill island, ask your friend to make their way to the quest hall (they do this by purchasing the 1 cp key from the Keymaster on the first island and trying it on the first island portals until it works).<br>
<br>
Have your friend find Dason Goldblade and hail him.  Dason will give your friend a book and at that point, ask your friend to stop until you give the word.  Take your key from the palace island and port yourself up to the windmill island.  Make your way to the inside of the windmill, just inside of the door.  You will be indifferent to the creatures on the windmill island so you don't need invis.  Once you are inside the windmill, things happen fast.  Have your friend give back the book to Dason Goldblade.  Dirkog Steelhand will pop, have your friend give him the 500 pp and get ready to go into action.  Inte Akira will pop and then give him the bits to get your FA.<br>
<br>
Do not delay on giving Inte the bits.  I completed my FA quest tonight and 2 minutes after I gave Inte all my pieces he despawned; I barely had time for a screenshot.  Your friend can exit the zone by jumping out of the quest hall and if you want, you can rejoin your group on the palace island or jump off the windmill island and join your friend in East FP for a well deserved beverage.<br>
<br>
If you did not leave a fresh corpse on the palace island (which happened to me) or forgot to leave a corpse at all, you can still get back to it (fighting strategy in the POA is based on pulling NPC's from the windmill island to the palace island).  You can jump from the windmill island to the palace island.  You will die, but with a quick rez, you are ready to go and can wow all your group with your fancy new barbecue stick  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  You have to pick your spot carefully and get a good running jump, but I made it and so can anyone else with reasonable luck.<br>
<br>
One thing to note is that there is some confusion about whether the windmill island is the 4th or 5th island.  It depends on which POA guide you read.  One of them assumes that you always bypass the Noble Djorn island and attack it last, even though you get the key to it on the first island, and therefore the windmill is the 4th island in that guide.  The other guide assumes that you do visit Noble Djorn as a pass through on your way and therefore, the windmill island is the 5th island in that guide.  Just make sure that everyone on your raid is in synch on where you are and there should be no problems.<br>
<br>
Good luck to all on completing the FA.<br>
<br>
Ragnorath D'Valoren<br>
Knight of Marr, 54th level<br>
